{{Infobox writer <!-- For more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]]. --> | name = Gerald Garrick Cunningham | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1945}} | birth_place = [[Dunedin]], [[South Island]], New Zealand | citizenship = New Zealand | period = 2003-present | occupation = [[Author]], [[photographer]], [[historian]], [[businessman]] }}
'''Gerald Garrick Cunningham''' (born 1945) is a New Zealand [[author]], [[photographer]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Gerald Cunningham|url=http://www.paperplus.co.nz/author/Gerald-Cunningham?i=156765|work=PaperPlus|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref> [[historian]] and [[businessman]].
Born in [[Dunedin]] in the [[South Island]] of New Zealand, he lived in that city and in [[Central Otago]], before moving to [[Auckland]] in 1957. Educated at [[Auckland Grammar School]] (1958–1962) he was employed by the [[Bank of New Zealand]], [[Wright Stephenson|Wright Stephenson & Co]] and Taylor Trading Company. In 1972 he established Company Forty Five Ltd., a business involved in the import, manufacture and wholesale of paintings and art prints to the retail trade throughout New Zealand. During 2001 he moved to the village of [[Lauder, New Zealand|Lauder]] in Central Otago.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gerald Cunningham (Author)|url=http://www.penguin.com.au/contributors/6462/gerald-cunningham|work=Penguin Books Australia|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref> Since that date he has written four books published by [[Reed Publishing|Reed Publishing NZ Ltd.]], a New Zealand company which was taken over by Penguin NZ, an offshoot of the multinational publisher, [[Penguin Group]], in 2009. A fifth book was published by Penguin NZ in 2009, with a sixth & seventh published by Bateman Publishing Ltd in 2011 & 2013.
==Works== *''Guide to the Otago Central Rail Trail''<ref>{{cite web|title=Guide to the Otago Central Rail Trail|url=http://www.penguin.co.nz/afa.asp?idWebPage=30233&ID=1973622&SID=57628676|work=Penguin Books (NZ)|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Zajkowski|first=Steph|title=Guide to the Otago Central Rail Trail: Book Review|url=http://tvnz.co.nz/lifestyle/guide-otago-central-rail-trail-book-review-3097276|work=TV NZ|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Travel book: Guide to the Central Otago Rail Trail|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/travel/news/article.cfm?c_id=7&objectid=10650407|accessdate=15 December 2012|newspaper=The New Zealand Herald|date=8 June 2010}}</ref><ref>Christchurch Press 27/10/2009</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Baker |first=Mary-Anne |title=Guide To The Central Otago Rail Trail |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/nelson-mail/entertainment/book-reviews/3199100/Guide-To-The-Central-Otago-Rail-Trail |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130224221533/http://www.stuff.co.nz/nelson-mail/entertainment/book-reviews/3199100/Guide-To-The-Central-Otago-Rail-Trail |dead-url=yes |archive-date=24 February 2013 |accessdate=15 December 2012 |newspaper=Fairfax NZ News |date=30 December 2009 }}</ref> Reed Publishing NZ Ltd, first published 2003, reprinted 2004,2005,2007 and republished by Penguin NZ in 2009. ({{ISBN|978 014 3202530}}) *''Guide to the Otago Goldfields Heritage Trail'', [[Blue Lake (Otago)]], Reed Publishing NZ Ltd, 2004, republished by Penguin NZ in 2008 ({{ISBN|9780143009948}}) *''Illustrated History of Central Otago & the Queenstown Lakes District'' [[Skippers Canyon]] Reed Publishing NZ Ltd., 2005 ({{ISBN|0 7900 1023 2}}) *''Otago Central Rail Trail - A Pictorial Journey''- Reed Publishing NZ Ltd., 2007 ({{ISBN|978 07900 1168 4}}) *''Central Otago - A Special Place''- Penguin NZ, 2009, ({{ISBN|9780 143 0 11118}}) *''The Taieri Gorge Railway'' - Bateman Publishing Ltd, 2011 ({{ISBN|978 1 86953 815 6}}) *''Skippers & The Sh