{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} {{Infobox UN resolution |number = 449 |organ = SC |date = 30 May |year = 1979 |meeting = 2,145 |code = S/RES/449 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/449(1979) |for = 14 |abstention = 0 |against = 0 |subject = Israel-Syrian Arab Republic |result = Adopted |image = Golan Heights Map.PNG |caption = UNDOF zone map }}
'''United Nations [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 449''', adopted on 30 May 1979, considered a report by the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] regarding the [[United Nations Disengagement Observer Force]]. The Council noted its efforts to establish a durable and just peace in the Middle East but also expressed its concern over the prevailing state of tension in the area.
The Resolution decided to call upon the parties concerned to immediately implement [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 338|Resolution 338]] (1973), it renewed the mandate of the Observer Force for another 6 months until 30 November 1979 and requested that the Secretary-General submit a report on the situation at the end of that period.
The resolution was adopted with 14 votes to none; [[People's Republic of China|China]] did not participate in the voting.
