'''William D. Irvine''' is a Canadian writer, historian and academic, currently Professor Emeritus of History at [[York University]]. He specializes in [[French history]] and has published a book on the [[Human Rights League (France)|Human Rights League]] of France (''Ligue des droits de l'homme''). He received his [[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]] degree in 1966 from the [[University of British Columbia]] and [[Ph.D.]] from [[Princeton University]]. As an author, he has largely been collected by libraries.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n78087750/ |title=Irvine, William D. |publisher=worldcat.org |accessdate=November 30, 2016}}</ref>
